(14, 'Privacy Policy', 'privacy-policy', '<div class="aboutus_section">\r\n<div class="container">\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12 guru_aboutus">\r\n<p>This policy relates to the privacy practices of Cambodia Indian Association (&ldquo;we&rdquo;, &ldquo;our&rdquo; or &ldquo;us&rdquo;) in connection with&nbsp;www.jeevanacharya.com.&nbsp; It sets out the basis on which any personal data that you provide to us, in connection with the Website will be processed and disclosed by us, in accordance with Irish data protection legislation.&nbsp; We are not responsible for the content or privacy practices of other websites.&nbsp; Any external links to other websites will be clearly identifiable as such.</p>\r\n<h3>Collection of Your Information</h3>\r\n<p>When you visit the Website as a browser we may collect certain information about your usage of the Website, including the IP address from which you access the Website, the date and time of your access to the Website and the pages you visit on the Website.&nbsp; Where you register or subscribe to the Website we may also collect personal data about you, including your name, address, email address, credit card or other payment details and other information from your correspondence with us.</p>\r\n<h3>Use of Your Information</h3>\r\n<p>We may use personal data relating to you to help make the Website more user-friendly, to provide the services and products requested by you, and to manage your registered account or subscription to the Website.&nbsp; Your personal data may also be used by us for the purposes of analytics and market research, in order to improve our Website and the products and services we offer to you.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>[We may also use your personal data to send you e-mail alerts about important changes or developments to the Website and to send you customer satisfaction or marketing surveys in relation to your subscription or registered account with us, in order to ascertain how we may improve our service to you.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We may also use your personal data to send you e-mail alerts with details of our products and services, which we feel may be of interest or relevance to you.</p>\r\n<h3>Disclosure of Your Information</h3>\r\n<p>We may disclose personal data relating to you to our agents, service providers and professional advisers and/or to such other third parties as may reasonably be required in connection with the purposes referred to in this Policy or as otherwise required or permitted by applicable law.&nbsp; This may involve the transfer of your personal data to a country outside of the Asian Economic Area where the level of data protection is not as high as in Cambodia.</p>\r\n<h3>Cookies</h3>\r\n<p>Please refer to our Cookies Policy which is incorporated into this Privacy Policy by this reference and is available&nbsp;here.</p>\r\n<h3>Retention of Your Information</h3>\r\n<p>We will only retain your personal data for as long as we require it for the purposes referred to in this Policy, unless we are required by applicable law or regulation to retain it for longer. If you cancel your subscription or delete your registered account for the Website and delete the Jeevanacharya mobile app from your mobile device we will delete any personal data we hold in relation to you as soon as reasonably possible and will immediately discontinue collecting any further personal data in relation to you.</p>\r\n<h3>Your Access and Amendment Rights </h3>\r\n<p>You have the right, subject to certain exemptions, to obtain a copy of any personal data which we hold about you (for which we may charge you a small fee) and to have inaccuracies in the information corrected. If you wish to avail of any of these rights, please contact us atinfo@jeevanacharya.com&nbsp;or Cambodia Indian Association, IOC Building, No.254, Monivong Blvd, Corner St.109, 6th Floor, Room No.007, Phnom Penh, Cambodia.&nbsp; In order to protect your privacy, you may also be asked to provide suitable proof of identification when making such a request.</p>\r\n<h3>Privacy Statement Changes</h3>\r\n<p>We may change this Privacy Policy from time to time, and in our sole discretion. &nbsp;We encourage you to frequently check this page for any changes to this Privacy Policy.&nbsp; Your continued use of this Website after any change in this Privacy Policy will constitute your acceptance of such change.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', '', 'Privacy Policy', 'Privacy Policy', 'Privacy Policy', 'full-width', 1, 0, '2017-05-13 08:37:46', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', ''),
